# Cyberland.Engine — XML documentation (`///`)

When editing files under `src/Cyberland.Engine/`, treat **public** API as documentation-first: IntelliSense, DocFX, and mod authors depend on it.

## Relationship to other rules

- **`cyberland-code-style`**: Use **`//` comments** inside methods for *why* and tricky logic. Use **`///` XML** for the **exported contract** (types, public members). Both can appear in the same file.
- **`cyberland-design-goals`**: Document **thread-safety** on types/members used from `IParallelSystem` or shared services (`IRenderer` submit APIs, etc.).
- **`cyberland-mod-host-architecture`**: In remarks on host/bootstrap types, keep **gameplay in mods**, not the host.

## Requirements for public API

1. **`/// <summary>`** on every new or touched **public** type and **public** member (including enum values and public struct fields).
2. Use **`<remarks>`** for audience context: who calls this (mod `IMod`, ECS system, render thread), and conventions (world space vs screen, radians vs degrees).
3. Use **`<see cref="..."/>`** to related types (`World`, `ComponentStore{T}`, `IRenderer`, `ModLoadContext`).
4. Use **`<param>`** / **`<returns>`** when names alone are not enough; state **units** (pixels, world Y-up vs screen Y-down — see `WorldScreenSpace`).
5. Prefer a short **`<example>`** with `<code lang="csharp">` on “hub” types (`GameApplication`, `World`, `IMod`, `ISystem`, `GameHostServices`, `IRenderer`) when it helps newcomers.
6. If **`GenerateDocumentationFile`** is enabled and **CS1591** is not suppressed, missing docs are **build warnings** — fix in the same change as API edits.
